<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-8274] methodMissing not executed when the delegate is an inner class</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8274</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Foo {
    
    void executeClosure(Closure c) {
        c.resolveStrategy = Closure.DELEGATE_ONLY
        c.delegate = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Bar()
        c.call()
    }

    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Bar {
        def methodMissing(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; name, args) {
            println name
        }
    }
}

Closure c = {
    go()
}

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Foo().executeClosure(c)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Executing the above results in:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;groovy.lang.MissingMethodException: No signature of method: Foo.go() is applicable for argument types: () values: []&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the Bar class is moved out of Foo, it works as I expect.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
